{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.9",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 9,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 9",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 9 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:2",
      "text": "“Truly I know that it is so: But how can a man be just before God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:3",
      "text": "If one wished to contend with him, one could not answer him once in a thousand times.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:4",
      "text": "He is wise in heart, and mighty in strength —who has hardened himself against him, and succeeded?—",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:5",
      "text": "he who removes mountains, and they know it not, when he overturns them in his anger;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:6",
      "text": "who shakes the earth out of its place, and its pillars tremble;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:7",
      "text": "who commands the sun, and it does not rise; who seals up the stars;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:8",
      "text": "who alone stretched out the heavens, and trampled the waves of the sea;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:9",
      "text": "who made the Bear and Orion, the Pleiades and the chambers of the south;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:10",
      "text": "who does great things beyond understanding, and marvelous things without number.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:11",
      "text": "Lo, he passes by me, and I see him not; he moves on, but I do not perceive him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:12",
      "text": "Behold, he snatches away; who can hinder him? Who will say to him, ‘What doest thou?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:13",
      "text": "“God will not turn back his anger; beneath him bowed the helpers of Rahab.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:14",
      "text": "How then can I answer him, choosing my words with him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:15",
      "text": "Though I am innocent, I cannot answer him; I must appeal for mercy to my accuser.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:16",
      "text": "If I summoned him and he answered me, I would not believe that he was listening to my voice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:17",
      "text": "For he crushes me with a tempest, and multiplies my wounds without cause;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:18",
      "text": "he will not let me get my breath, but fills me with bitterness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:19",
      "text": "If it is a contest of strength, behold him! If it is a matter of justice, who can summon him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:20",
      "text": "Though I am innocent, my own mouth would condemn me; though I am blameless, he would prove me perverse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:21",
      "text": "I am blameless; I regard not myself; I loathe my life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:22",
      "text": "It is all one; therefore I say, he destroys both the blameless and the wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:23",
      "text": "When disaster brings sudden death, he mocks at the calamity of the innocent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:24",
      "text": "The earth is given into the hand of the wicked; he covers the faces of its judges— if it is not he, who then is it?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:25",
      "text": "“My days are swifter than a runner; they flee away, they see no good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:26",
      "text": "They go by like skiffs of reed, like an eagle swooping on the prey.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:27",
      "text": "If I say, ‘I will forget my complaint, I will put off my sad countenance, and be of good cheer,’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:28",
      "text": "I become afraid of all my suffering, for I know thou wilt not hold me innocent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:29",
      "text": "I shall be condemned; why then do I labor in vain?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:30",
      "text": "If I wash myself with snow, and cleanse my hands with lye,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:31",
      "text": "yet thou wilt plunge me into a pit, and my own clothes will abhor me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:32",
      "text": "For he is not a man, as I am, that I might answer him, that we should come to trial together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:33",
      "text": "There is no umpire between us, who might lay his hand upon us both.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:34",
      "text": "Let him take his rod away from me, and let not dread of him terrify me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.9.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 9,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 9:35",
      "text": "Then I would speak without fear of him, for I am not so in myself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
